rets of his creative mechanisms were only producing blanks, and this frustrating state of affairs had stretched his nerves to the end of the tether. 
\par <#/>The young man's name was Martin Gumba. <#/>Not long before, he had taken the creative world by storm with his play, }{\i\fs24\lang2057 Submission Unlimited}{\fs24\lang2057 
, a sorrowful yam about the plight of workers in a set-up where all their rights were ruthlessly trampled upon by employers with hearts of stone. 
\par <#/>The play had opened to unusually flattering reviews, and its success was a miracle of modern times, especially for a relatively new addition to the theatre world. <#/>Though apparently never published, for whatever reasons, }{\i\fs24\lang2057 
Submission Unlimited}{\fs24\lang2057  to this day remains one of the best original plays to have come out of this country. 
