\par Few people in this country can match the contributions of Okumba Miruka to the world of culture and the arts over the years. <#/>Literary and art critic }{\i\fs24\lang2057 par}{\fs24\lang2057  }{\i\fs24\lang2057 excellence, }{\fs24\lang2057 
this trained teacher seems to possess boundless energy, and his contributions in both the print and electronic media are impressive. 
\par <#/>Explaining his philosophy in life recently, Okumba, as he is commonly known, said determination was a critical prerequisite for success in any field. <#/>It is obvious his stamina has been fed by an intrinsic }{\i\fs24\lang2057 never}{\fs24\lang2057  
}{\i\fs24\lang2057 say die }{\fs24\lang2057 attitude and constitution. 
\par <#/>"The river must reach its destination," he says, "any barriers we find in life must be overcome!"
\par True to his philosophy, Okumba has overcome heavy odds to become a leading actor in the country's intellectual forums. 
\par <#/>Having attended Kenyatta University and studied English language, literature and education, his intellectual endeavours have recently culminated in the publication of}{\i\fs24\lang2057  Encounter with Oral Literature}{\fs24\lang2057 
, a book that even his former dons at Kenyatta will agree is one of the best on the subject. 
\par <#/>The 194-page thoroughly documented book follows }{\i\fs24\lang2057 A Dictionary}{\fs24\lang2057  }{\i\fs24\lang2057 Of Oral Literature}{\fs24\lang2057  which he co-authored with Leteipa ole Sunkuli. <#/>This book published by Hein
emann (now East African Educational Publishers) in 1990, and it has now become an indispensable reference book for teachers of oral literature. 
\par <#/>Okumba, who is the vice-chairman of the Kenya Oral Literature Association (KOLA), has also published}{\i\fs24\lang2057  Handling Technical Terminology in Teaching Oral Literature}{\fs24\lang2057  for KOLA. 
\par <#/>This work, published earlier this year, is also bound to be extremely useful to teachers of the genre. 
\par <X_>}{\v\fs24\lang2057 At present, the indefatigable Okumba is editing an anthology for KOLA titled }{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 The Bearded Woman}{\v\fs24\lang2057 , as well as putting the final touches to }{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 Oral Literature of the Luo}{
\v\fs24\lang2057 , another anthology soon to be published by East African Educational Publishers.
\par Okumba's prolific literary output has also seen his academic papers and poems published in numerous forums, and his literary criticism is a common feature in the media, including this newspaper.
\par He has also}{\b\v\fs24\lang2057  }{\v\fs24\lang2057 been the brains behind the Kenya Broadcasting Corporation programme, }{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 Talking Literature}{\v\fs24\lang2057  and }{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 Preview, }{\v\fs24\lang2057 
a programme focussing on theatre.
\par Discussing his astounding production, 32-year-old Okumba explains that creativity has always been in his blood. During his secondary years at Cardinal Otunga High School, he was the editor of }{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 The Weaverbird}{\v\fs24\lang2057 
, a weekly newsletter, as well as }{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 Cardinal Points}{\v\fs24\lang2057 , the monthly school magazine. 
\par Later at Kenyatta University, he was to become the chairman of the Kibera Poetry Association, named after the lecturer and author, Leonard Kibera.
\par In addition, Okumba has been on the panel of the Kenya Institute of Educa\-tion Oral Literature since 1987.
\par Besides practising freelance journal\-ism, Okumba also worked as a staff reporter for }{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 The Weekly Review }{\v\fs24\lang2057 at one time.
\par At present, Okumba is a consultant on gender training and other related projects. His efforts in gender-sensitive initiati
ves have seen him research and compile Gender Perspectives in Luo Short Forms, a major undertaking under the auspices of the Kenya Oral Literature Association.
\par While earlier works by such oral literature specialists as Wanjiku Kabira, Austin Bukenya, Kicha
mu Akivaga, and the late Jane Nandwa, have been basically anthologies, Okumba has set out to provide a text that discusses and seriously analyses issues pertinent to the subject.
